hat...</span><hr size=1> Its not like enchanters there you can pick a place. mage have to find a place with a good placed elemantal too.<br>
<br>
Charm works fine, in my experience if you able to find a good spot at the portals your liely to stay alive increase with like 1000%.<br>
Park pet near portal, pull mob to pet, stand a bit from pet and mob and let them fight.<br>
Pet wins, loot quick, use portal and gate.<br>
Run back in a set up again. <br>
After a few times this only take a few mins and you have not very much problem kill 8-10 mobs before repop.<br>
With this tactic if charm breaks you have a good chance to use portal and gate, you will be out of range from mobs agro range and you wont be summoned, gate to clear agro and try again.<br>
<br>
Of course don't count on staying alive for more than 1 hour at a time, sometimes mobs summon you and your pet often kill you faster than you can react.<br>
I never bother try and recharm if it breaks, it fail more than it works.<br>
In my opinion this is a really fun way to play, it is exactly how charm should be used (in my opinion), the risk is huge, you have to pay total a attention, you need to know exactly where to pull.<br>
If something fail we have have a mob that summon to deal with, the pathing not as bad as in HoH (easy to avoid  totaly to get hit while you recharm), no fanzy 3500 rune to help you and most of all our pets are no wimps because we have to haste them to make sure they win.<br>
<br>
Charm should never be nerfed, it is nothing wrong with charm or the ability to haste a charmed mob or even the resist adjust. <br>
I hope Verant don't do a quickfix to nerf charm (infact our charm and mezz should be upgraded to work on higher levels to make it usefull in more places) and instead fix the issues with bad pathing, and mobs that don't summon. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=salashpenumbra>Salash Penumbra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 418<br> <font color=#333333>(2/7/03 7:23:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1833.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Doubt that...</span><hr size=1> The main place for soloing mages is BoT. Elementals spawn uncommonly. Over 70% of mobs you'll be killing with your pet will be melee giant, ie summoners.<br>
